    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Read-only verification that `PaneEventBus.ts` accepts the new `memory` channel without code changes. Per ADR-030 v2 amendment § "Required implementation updates" bullet 2, the bus's Set-keyed registry is channel-string-agnostic. This task confirms that assumption empirically via grep + read.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform frontend developer. Verifying ADR-030 v2 invariant that bus implementation does not need extension for new channel members.</role>

  <goal>
    Documented confirmation that `PaneEventBus.ts` switch / channel-dispatch logic accepts `memory` without code changes — either because logic is string-keyed (no enum/literal whitelist) or because TypeScript channel-parameter typing already widens to `PaneChannel`. No code edits required by this task.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per ADR-030 v2 amendment, the bus is intended to be channel-string-agnostic (Set-keyed registry per channel name). Task 060 extended `PaneChannel` to include `memory`. This task verifies that the bus's TypeScript signatures (which use `PaneChannel` as the parameter type) automatically accept `memory` without any code change to `PaneEventBus.ts` itself. If a hardcoded switch / type-narrowing surfaces, file a finding (do NOT modify here — main session will route to a follow-up task).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/PaneEventBus.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/PaneEventBusContext.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/usePaneEvent.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/useDispatchPaneEvent.ts</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-030 v2">Bus implementation is channel-string-agnostic per amendment bullet 2.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Read-only verification — no code edits in this task. Findings filed to notes/handoffs/.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-030">Channels remain a closed union of exactly 5 members. Do not add a 6th.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/architecture/stateful-chat-architecture.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-030-pane-event-bus.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `PaneEventBus.ts` end-to-end.</step>
    <step order="2">Grep for `switch (channel)` / `case 'workspace'` / `case 'context'` / hardcoded channel-literal narrowing in PaneEventBus.ts + Context.tsx + usePaneEvent.ts + useDispatchPaneEvent.ts.</step>
    <step order="3">If hardcoded channel-literal switches found → file a finding in notes/handoffs/061-findings.md listing the file:line and the fix needed; main session will route to a follow-up task.</step>
    <step order="4">If no hardcoded switches found → confirm bus logic uses `PaneChannel`-typed parameter and Set-keyed registry; document in notes/handoffs/061-findings.md.</step>
    <step order="5">Run `npx tsc --noEmit` in `src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/` to confirm zero type errors after task 060's union extension.</step>
    <step order="6">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 061 → ✅; current-task.md → next task.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">PaneEventBus.ts and peer files</tool>
    <tool name="Grep">Locate switch/case/channel-literal narrowing patterns</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">npx tsc --noEmit</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="docs">notes/handoffs/061-findings.md — verification result (clean OR list of findings)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`PaneEventBus.ts` source read end-to-end and grep results documented.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`npx tsc --noEmit` exits 0 in Spaarke.AI.Widgets.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">notes/handoffs/061-findings.md created with either "clean" confirmation or itemized findings.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No code edits made to bus files in this task.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <ui-tests>
    <test scope="type-check">`npx tsc --noEmit` — bus accepts `memory` channel parameter through PaneChannel union.</test>
  </ui-tests>

  <notes>
    Parallel-safe with 062, 063, 064 (separate concerns; no file overlap — read-only on bus files; type-check and build are separate).
